          <div>
            <div class="faq-q">Can I get a pilot mortgage as a first-year regional First Officer?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">Yes. The Minimum Guaranteed Hours (MGTH) method qualifies you on your contractual guarantee from day one — no two-year flying history required. With a conventional 5% down loan or an FHA 3.5% down loan, most first-year regional FOs qualify in the $250,000–$450,000 home range depending on the airline and base. If you're a veteran, the VA loan eliminates the down payment and PMI entirely.</div>
