        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-num">02</div>
          <div>
            <div class="faq-q">Will lenders count my per diem on a pilot mortgage application?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">Most won't. We will, when you have a 24-month history of receiving it (Fannie Mae's selling guide allows it; the issue is whether the lender understands how to document it). On a typical regional Captain's income, per diem adds $150–250/mo of qualifying — translating to roughly $25,000–$45,000 more home you can qualify for.</div>
