        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-num">03</div>
          <div>
            <div class="faq-q">I'm about to upgrade to Captain. Can I qualify for a pilot mortgage on my new pay before I start?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">Yes — this is exactly what Method 3 (future-rate qualification) is for. With your upgrade award letter, confirmed base assignment, and contractual Captain hourly rate, we qualify you on the new pay rather than the FO pay you're currently earning. Most upgrades can be qualified 60–90 days before the new pay starts. This often increases your qualifying income by $50,000–$80,000. Run the math on our <a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-calculator/jumbo-loan/" style="color: var(--blue); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px;">jumbo calculator</a> to see what the new payment looks like.</div>
